title: These are the 9 'dictionary' stocks investors should hold onto as the reopening trade stages a comeback, Fundstrat says
text: Throughout the COVID-19 pandemic, Fundstrat's Tom Lee has advised clients to buy the "epicenter" stocks in anticipation of a successful vaccine being developed. "Epicenter" stocks are those that were most harmed by the onset of the pandemic and are now set to benefit from the reopening of the economy. These include airlines, casinos, restaurants and so on.Â
